narrative /ˈnærətɪv/

(narratives) 

1. N-COUNT A narrative is a story or an account of a series of events. 故事; 叙事 

例： ...a fast-moving narrative. …一个快节奏的叙事。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Narrative is the description of a series of events, usually in a novel. (尤指小说中的) 记叙 

例： Neither author was very strong on narrative. 两位作者在记叙方面都不强。

